track_notes:
11.5m (18.5 Km) / 3700ft (1128m) ascent 
The route uses the footpath from the back of the Patterdale Hotel to the Hole in the Wall (Wainwright Birkhouse Moor very close) then we visit one of my favourite Wainwrights Catstye Cam. We then traverse Swirral Edge (Care needed but less riskier than Striding Edge) to Helvellyn. We then cross Nethermost and Dollywaggon Pikes (Wainwrights) returning via Grisedale into Glenridding and ending again at the Patterdale Hotel. (Recommended for short breaks for bagging the Lake Districts Eastern and Far Eastern Fells - nothing fancy but excellent value for money - entertainment Thursdays & Saturdays!)
For more info see Walk 6 on wainwrightsontheair.blogspot.co.uk or view my other alternative routes instead!
track_title: Helvellyn circular from The Patterdale Hotel

track_notes:
9.3m (15 km) 3250ft (991m) ascent.
You may start this route from adjacent to the Youth Hostel (limited parking and partly unmetalled road) near the worked out Greenside Mines or add a bit on if you wish, and start from Glenridding itself. The interesting route takes you past the spoil heaps and on to the Sticks Pass. You go over the Wainwrights of Raise and Whiteside before you surmount Helvellyn so why not operate from them for WOTA as you pass thorugh? After visiting Helvellyn you return via Striding Edge and the Wainwright of Birkhouse Moor. The stepped path down from Birkhouse Moo which is hard on the knees delivers you back to the Youth Hostel or you can turn right at Miresbeck to go into Glenridding directly instead. For more detail look at Walk 15 on 
wainwrightsontheair.blogspot.co.uk

14.8m/23.8km 5260ft/1603m ascent.
This route which avoids Swirral and Striding Edges is what SOTA enthusiasts call the Lakeland 44 point winter round. With the winter bonus that is what it is worth. Starting from the back of the Patterdale Hotel climb Thornhow End to reach St Sunday Crag (96 mins). Cofa Pike is traversed next - care needed but looks worse than it is when you reach it on the way to Fairfield. Now drop down to Grisedale Hause and follow the wall up the steep side of Seat Sandal. From here drop down to Cairn (on the map) and cross Willie Wife Moor to reach the mian path coming up from Thirlmere. This takes you on to Helvellyn. The shortest way back is via one of the edges - if not safe visit the Wainwrights of Nethermost and Dollywagon to take you down to Grisedale and then back to Patterdale. If you have the energy why not drive to Little Mell Fell for another 5 points and then if you have further stamina add on Great Mell Fell to win you a total of 54 points in the day
track_title: Helvellyn - Seat Sandal (LD-022) - Fairfield (LD-007) - St Sunday Crag (LD-010)
Helvellyn from Wathburn Church parking place

track_notes: From Swirls car park, head over footbridge and follow obvious and maintained path up the summit. Walk takes circa 2 hours.
